Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Symbolic Token Encoding", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"7b8b0254-06ee-42c5-a0ed-55959cf4f34e"],

Cell["\<\
Input nodes can specify an encoder function that converts external inputs to \
sparse sets. Similarly, output nodes can decode internal representations. \
This software framework includes a library of commonly used encoders and \
decoders. Additional, user-defined encoders can be plugged in directly \
without requiring modifications of the core framework.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"afe383f7-9d82-4949-a471-a26f7c6b1778"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Generic token encoder and decoder", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"56ec7da0-44fb-4b7e-aa3c-5b35bb11686d"],

Cell["\<\
The \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]codec\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] module encodes \
distinct input data into random SHRs. This is the standard method of \
representation symbolic tokens. Plugged into an output node, it decodes the \
set to the original data format.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0ac56cc2-8d92-4061-84b4-30e191005893"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

