Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Category encoding", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"def6a4e1-91fe-4e9c-9e22-486cbc900cca"],

Cell["\<\
For encoding a small number K of categories, enumerated as integers from 0 to \
K-1,  an encoding that produces non-overlapping representations often works \
better than the generic symbolic encoder discussed above. Here we choose a \
population P=10 to encode K=10 numbers. This requires a minimum dimension N = \
K*P = 100:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9061c8f4-fdea-428c-a5d2-e8a0235351d1"],

