Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Encoding Numeric Data", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"611610be-a51f-414e-a335-330cc59cb5f4"],

Cell["\<\
This framework includes multiple SDR encoders for numeric data.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5ec5b2c0-cbf2-4958-a7fb-7e8654f7e4c5"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Vector encoding", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"38cc6634-ea66-46ee-a1c5-a7bdd6790657"],

Cell["\<\
The general-purpose vector encoder transforms dense numeric data to SDRs. It \
performs a random projection onto a hyperdimensional space by multiplying the \
input with a random sparse binary matrix, followed by kWTA to control the \
output sparsity. This implementation of kWTA, using the connection\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s population as the value of k, may return more than k \
elements in case of a tie between the top-k elements.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6e912295-0481-4f82-847f-e6086eafc4ef"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

