Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Multiplexing and Temporal Gating", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"fafa2d3f-f7ea-423c-9e4f-c9d296ef16f8"],

Cell["\<\
By default, invoking a circuit\[CloseCurlyQuote]s function triggers one \
evaluation cycle. Multiple cycles with the same input (preprocessed and \
encoded),  or alternatively with zero inputs (an empty list for each function \
argument) can be  triggered  by setting the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]multiplex\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] option in the circuit\[CloseCurlyQuote]s dataflow \
description. The multiplexing specification is a string of \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]1\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]0\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]. Each \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]1\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] triggers an evaluation cycle with the same repeated \
input. Each \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]0\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] triggers a cycle \
with empty inputs, during which only the circuit-internal state is processed.\
\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3c0da086-2afa-4a30-8ae7-91fbb9071a89"],

Cell["\<\
This circuit triggers three cycles with the same input. We tag the path with \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]?\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] to inspect the dataflow:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"79016725-eb80-41cc-9f8e-2b194104ca26"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

