Cell["\<\
Zero-padding, specified by a string of the form \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]1000...\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote],  is typically used to \
flush the delay line in embedded circuits that take multiple cycles to \
process an individual input. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"47cb715c-ff12-4562-96ca-a1d937136b8b"],

Cell["\<\
With this dataflow graph, inputs by default are delayed by one cycle. \
Zero-padding with one additional cycle removes the delay:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9852371e-57eb-4309-b9b1-f2251ae5f6d3"],

