Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Stochastic Subsampling", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2a3364b5-0849-49f6-ad4a-dbcef7c9d8dc"],

Cell["\<\
Stochastic subsampling  is a fundamental mechanism operating on sparse binary \
representations. Within this software framework,  subsampling mechanisms  are \
integrated into various component types, as well as directly into the data \
transport mechanism  (pathways). \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"27b7f620-0840-4bfa-91eb-04160b56601e"],

Cell["\<\
A path tagged with \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]R\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] reduces \
the  signal to at most it\[CloseCurlyQuote]s specified population. This \
mechanism acts as a rate limiter during signal transport:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1532ac4b-9f7c-444e-b22b-999f741195af"],

