Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Recurrence", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6acfef1a-29d7-43e1-9b7e-b95d45133c27"],

Cell["\<\
Recurrence -- a fundamental property of cognitive architectures -- is \
characterized by cyclic connections in the circuit graph, integrating data \
across synchronized clock cycles through feedback loops. Any such feedback \
system relies on stochastic signal decimation to  prevent runaway activity. \
This framework supports various mechanisms for managing sparsity in recurrent \
architectures: stochastic rate limiting located in the data transport logic \
(pathways) or
within delay nodes, k-winners-take-all mechanims applied in pathway \
integration or in temporally integrated signals,  and the update rules that \
govern the recurrent network encapsulated within auto-associative memory \
components.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a211e5e7-4ec0-4348-8525-e6edf0874e53"],

Cell["\<\
Here is a most basic recurrent circuit consisting of a single delay node. The \
two incoming signals are merged into a multiset. Rate limiting is applied \
within the circuit component.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cf24cedd-0af2-4164-aad7-b8fc1c3ce333"],

