Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["K-Winners-Take-All", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2a2c5f13-d0f1-4a16-a571-0cb1dd849dba"],

Cell["\<\
K-winner-take-all (kWTA) is a competitive neural network mechanism where only \
the top k most active neurons are allowed to fire, while all others are \
suppressed to zero. Translated to this computational framework, kWTA converts \
a multiset to a set. This ubiquitous algorithm drives the topological \
associative memory algorithm, is used in SDR encoding, and path merging. In 
addition, it is implemented as a circuit component which applies to kWTA to \
signals within a sliding time window.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3128f528-ea49-4fc1-958a-15c61e9981bc"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Path merging with kWTA", "Subsubsection",ExpressionUUID->"facbe457-02f9-413e-805a-bdfce84233d6"],

Cell["\<\
Merging paths where at least one path is tagged with \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]k\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] applies the kWTA algorithm, using the path\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s population parameter as the ranking parameter. \
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0954146c-b7c5-490a-b6ab-f768a494c01a"],

